<plot>BAD T!MING is the story of Chiku, a respected Zambian social activist who is the leader of a U.N. Committee to improve the Future of the African Child. He is the son of a Ngoni chief who is to marry the daughter of a Tonga leader. The police come to arrest Chiku at his wedding, his bride is horrified to discover that he is accused of raping a neighborhood girl. Chiku begins an epic struggle to restore himself personally and professionally. A tale of failure, corruption, forgiveness and redemption, BAD T!MING reveals the rich Zambian culture in the first feature film made in that country.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?056066</url></doc>
